				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>This is, as usual, beautifully paced and observed: the slightly detached tone works very well to convey the tension between the cute and the sinister. I really enjoyed the construction of the story through small details which build up into a horribly compelling picture. Bonus points for &#8220;sashay&#8221; and &#8220;Examine, ye, my untouchable beauty&#8221;, which are wonderfully atmospheric.</p>
<p>If I have to nit-pick, which really the piece doesn&#8217;t merit, for me the sentence &#8220;the glowing mass where Jack‚Äôs upper intestinal tract would have been if one could see soft tissue on an x-ray&#8221; doesn&#8217;t quite work, it feels a bit clumsy and not entirely meaningful.</p>
